                    "@type": "Question",
                    "name": "How many stock market sectors are there?",
                    "acceptedAnswer": {
                        "@type": "Answer",
                        "text": "A stock market sector is a group of stocks that have a lot in common with each other, usually because they are in similar industries. We categorize stocks into sectors to make it easy to compare companies that have similar business models. When investing, you can choose from stocks within the sectors that interest you. Sectors also make it easier to compare which stocks are making the most money. This helps you make decisions about what your next investments will be.",
